1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:31,010 --> 00:01:37,020
[Fireworks of My Heart]

3
00:01:37,110 --> 00:01:40,110
[Episode 16]

4
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,960
Our recent rescues have revealed

5
00:01:42,060 --> 00:01:43,479
many shortcomings,

6
00:01:44,259 --> 00:01:45,780
especially with regard to medical rescue.

7
00:01:47,289 --> 00:01:49,140
What do you guys think?

8
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:50,500
Let’s talk about it.

9
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,300
Supervisor.

10
00:01:52,539 --> 00:01:53,020
Here's the thing.

11
00:01:53,820 --> 00:01:55,460
If it's just stopping bleeding or bandaging,

12
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:56,740
we can definitely manage.

13
00:01:56,780 --> 00:01:57,170
Right?

14
00:01:57,380 --> 00:01:57,580
Yes.

15
00:01:57,580 --> 00:01:58,289
But when it comes to

16
00:01:58,289 --> 00:01:59,100
more complicated wounds,

17
00:01:59,180 --> 00:02:00,500
how are we supposed to deal?

18
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:01,540
Besides,

19
00:02:01,780 --> 00:02:03,660
it's not a firefighter's job

20
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:05,060
to treat injuries.

21
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:06,420
More importantly, we don't know how.

22
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:07,980
Supervisor, Chief.

23
00:02:07,980 --> 00:02:08,900
I have an idea.

24
00:02:09,009 --> 00:02:09,500
Go ahead.

25
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:10,740
Can we

26
00:02:10,740 --> 00:02:12,170
discuss with the medical unit

27
00:02:12,170 --> 00:02:13,180
to have the ambulance arrive at the scene

28
00:02:13,180 --> 00:02:14,300
when the firetruck arrives?

29
00:02:14,660 --> 00:02:16,420
The injured can only

30
00:02:16,420 --> 00:02:17,300
receive prompt treatment

31
00:02:17,300 --> 00:02:18,540
when professional doctors and nurses are around.

32
00:02:18,820 --> 00:02:19,530
Supervisor.

33
00:02:20,260 --> 00:02:21,410
We have thought about

34
00:02:21,410 --> 00:02:22,579
Dapeng's idea before.

35
00:02:23,579 --> 00:02:24,500
For example, when we arrive at the scene

36
00:02:24,500 --> 00:02:25,380
see people who are injured,

37
00:02:25,410 --> 00:02:26,450
we call 120.

38
00:02:26,450 --> 00:02:27,290
That's no problem at all.

39
00:02:27,820 --> 00:02:29,540
But for ambulances to remain on standby every day

40
00:02:29,540 --> 00:02:30,060
and go on missions

41
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:30,740
with us

42
00:02:30,740 --> 00:02:31,620
isn't realistic.

43
00:02:32,020 --> 00:02:33,420
After all, we're not under the same system.

44
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:35,140
What's the use of saying all that?

45
00:02:35,780 --> 00:02:36,940
He's right.

46
00:02:38,210 --> 00:02:39,180
What do you think?

47
00:02:41,170 --> 00:02:42,500
We encounter many complicated situations

48
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,460
at rescue sites.

49
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:44,820
It's not hard

50
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:45,940
to think of ideas.

51
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:47,820
It's too hard to implement them.

52
00:02:50,470 --> 00:02:52,060
It's worth doing difficult things.

53
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:54,780
I want to try.

54
00:03:00,330 --> 00:03:01,010
Training!

55
00:03:01,130 --> 00:03:01,660
Come on.

56
00:03:01,860 --> 00:03:02,820
Let's go.

57
00:03:03,780 --> 00:03:04,460
It's too hot.

58
00:03:04,660 --> 00:03:05,340
Let's go.

59
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,650
[Request to Establish a Joint Firefighting and Medical Rescue Team]

60
00:03:13,720 --> 00:03:15,220
You want to set up a joint firefighting and medical

61
00:03:15,220 --> 00:03:16,820
rescue team.

62
00:03:18,790 --> 00:03:20,420
Is this a spontaneous idea

63
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:22,110
or something you've been thinking about for a while?

64
00:03:23,460 --> 00:03:23,980
Commissar.

65
00:03:24,390 --> 00:03:26,340
During the shanty town fire,

66
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:28,180
the call we received said

67
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:30,340
that it's a demolition area

68
00:03:30,340 --> 00:03:31,340
where no one lives.

69
00:03:31,630 --> 00:03:32,820
But when we arrived at the scene,

70
00:03:32,820 --> 00:03:33,940
we still found a child

71
00:03:33,940 --> 00:03:35,180
who was severely injured.

72
00:03:36,079 --> 00:03:37,060
After we

73
00:03:37,060 --> 00:03:38,460
gave her emergency treatment,

74
00:03:38,740 --> 00:03:39,860
we sent her to the hospital.

75
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,180
A few days ago,

76
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,060
we found a traveler

77
00:03:43,060 --> 00:03:43,860
deep in the mountains

78
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:44,850
who was severely injured.

79
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:46,500
We had to use a satellite phone

80
00:03:46,500 --> 00:03:47,980
to ask for help from a doctor.

81
00:03:49,140 --> 00:03:50,100
These two incidents

82
00:03:50,100 --> 00:03:51,100
really affected me.

83
00:03:51,370 --> 00:03:53,260
If there had been medical staff

84
00:03:53,260 --> 00:03:54,260
alongside us,

85
00:03:54,380 --> 00:03:55,660
we could have managed the incidents

86
00:03:55,660 --> 00:03:57,500
more efficiently,

87
00:03:58,230 --> 00:03:59,300
and also have reduced

88
00:03:59,300 --> 00:04:00,100
casualties.

89
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:02,530
I have been thinking about this recently,

90
00:04:02,980 --> 00:04:04,660
but also for a long time.

91
00:04:06,720 --> 00:04:07,940
If a doctor could

92
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:08,940
give prompt treatment at the scene,

93
00:04:08,940 --> 00:04:10,060
that would be best.

94
00:04:12,150 --> 00:04:14,020
However, the medical and firefighting departments

95
00:04:14,020 --> 00:04:16,060
are separate right now.

96
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:18,019
There is a certain time lag

97
00:04:18,019 --> 00:04:19,540
in our coordination.

98
00:04:19,779 --> 00:04:20,660
But it's also

99
00:04:20,660 --> 00:04:21,740
under control.

100
00:04:22,690 --> 00:04:24,340
If we can conduct more rescue trainings

101
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:26,220
for the doctors,

102
00:04:26,380 --> 00:04:27,420
we can also

103
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:28,580
promote the collaboration

104
00:04:28,780 --> 00:04:29,740
between the two departments.

105
00:04:29,740 --> 00:04:30,690
That's a good thing.

106
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,100
Your suggestion

107
00:04:34,100 --> 00:04:35,340
is good,

108
00:04:35,820 --> 00:04:36,740
but

109
00:04:36,980 --> 00:04:38,659
for doctors and firefighters

110
00:04:38,659 --> 00:04:40,340
to enter the scene at the same time

111
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,930
is no joke.

112
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:43,780
How can we improve their ability

113
00:04:43,780 --> 00:04:45,100
to adapt to conditions at the scene

114
00:04:45,140 --> 00:04:46,900
and ensure their safety?

115
00:04:47,930 --> 00:04:48,820
Have you thought about that?

116
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:51,340
Let firefighters conduct targeted training

117
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:53,260
for the medical workers

118
00:04:53,260 --> 00:04:55,060
to set rules for safety.

119
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:58,380
It seems you're confident

120
00:04:58,610 --> 00:04:59,850
about the training.

121
00:05:01,260 --> 00:05:01,900
By the way,

122
00:05:04,540 --> 00:05:06,180
I have a proposal.

123
00:05:16,470 --> 00:05:18,320
You came well-prepared.

124
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:22,940
You've always wanted to work on the ground.

125
00:05:23,060 --> 00:05:24,380
I was afraid you wouldn't adapt to the new place.

126
00:05:25,650 --> 00:05:26,140
How is it?

127
00:05:26,220 --> 00:05:27,780
How's your partnership with Song Yan?

128
00:05:27,820 --> 00:05:29,130
He helped me a lot

129
00:05:29,490 --> 00:05:30,730
and is very supportive.

130
00:05:32,940 --> 00:05:34,580
I know his temper the best.

131
00:05:34,780 --> 00:05:37,240
It's not easy for you to partner together.

132
00:05:39,980 --> 00:05:40,620
Alright.

133
00:05:41,659 --> 00:05:43,020
As for your proposal,

134
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:44,780
I will request for approval from my superiors

135
00:05:45,260 --> 00:05:46,980
to make Shilitai Station

136
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,250
a testing unit

137
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,659
for cooperation with the city hospital.

138
00:05:49,780 --> 00:05:50,570
Thank you, Commissar.

139
00:05:52,350 --> 00:05:55,110
[Internal Medicine] [Infectious Diseases] [Respiratory Disease Center]

140
00:05:53,420 --> 00:05:54,340
Thank you

141
00:05:54,340 --> 00:05:55,260
for specially making the trip here.

142
00:05:55,260 --> 00:05:56,700
I hope our departments

143
00:05:56,780 --> 00:05:57,780
will have a successful cooperation.

144
00:05:58,180 --> 00:05:58,980
Also,

145
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:00,180
you should consider

146
00:06:00,300 --> 00:06:01,490
a media report.

147
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,970
It's publicity after all.

148
00:06:03,540 --> 00:06:04,460
Thank you, Deputy President Liu.

149
00:06:04,460 --> 00:06:05,180
See you.

150
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:06,330
See you.

151
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:13,580
They only do projects to look good.

152
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,060
But it's fine as long as

153
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:16,300
it doesn't interfere with us doing real work.

154
00:06:16,460 --> 00:06:17,580
What work?

155
00:06:18,420 --> 00:06:20,020
I've never agreed with the plan

156
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:21,340
to set up a joint rescue team.

157
00:06:21,540 --> 00:06:22,820
I stand by my position.

158
00:06:23,090 --> 00:06:24,100
The doctors and nurses

159
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:25,300
are not familiar with fires.

160
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:27,060
They can't operate practically there.

161
00:06:27,130 --> 00:06:28,140
We didn't say

162
00:06:28,140 --> 00:06:29,620
they must enter the scene of the fire.

163
00:06:29,790 --> 00:06:31,220
Can't I train them well

164
00:06:32,020 --> 00:06:33,450
to watch out for their safety?

165
00:06:33,710 --> 00:06:34,940
It's easy for you to say.

166
00:06:35,310 --> 00:06:36,659
Are the doctors and nurses

167
00:06:36,740 --> 00:06:37,740
in the hospital's system

168
00:06:37,740 --> 00:06:38,659
or the fire station's?

169
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:40,900
If there's a conflict between the work

170
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,820
in the hospital and the fire station,

171
00:06:41,850 --> 00:06:42,980
what are they supposed to prioritize?

172
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:45,340
That's why I always say

173
00:06:46,060 --> 00:06:47,260
you're idealistic.

174
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:48,980
I'm not idealistic.

175
00:06:49,340 --> 00:06:50,500
Let's try it out first.

176
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,180
Let's some professional medical staff

177
00:06:52,180 --> 00:06:53,060
to cooperate with the firefighters.

178
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:54,180
Isn't that good?

179
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,420
You're getting more and more far-fetched.

180
00:06:55,420 --> 00:06:56,420
Let's get back to the point.

181
00:06:56,659 --> 00:06:58,100
Now that the joint rescue team has been formed,

182
00:06:58,100 --> 00:06:59,180
it needs you to guide—

183
00:07:00,060 --> 00:07:00,820
Sorry.

184
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,090
What a coincidence.

185
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:09,140
Why are you here?

186
00:07:10,170 --> 00:07:10,900
We

187
00:07:10,900 --> 00:07:12,020
came down

188
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,020
because of the joint rescue team.

189
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:14,540
Let me introduce.

190
00:07:14,620 --> 00:07:15,780
Song Yan, our Station Chief.

191
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:22,510
Do you know each other?

192
00:07:23,340 --> 00:07:24,100
No.
Yes.

193
00:07:26,440 --> 00:07:27,440
Yes, I do.
No.

194
00:07:31,420 --> 00:07:33,130
I'll leave you to it. I'm leaving.

195
00:07:38,170 --> 00:07:39,060
What's going on?

196
00:07:41,650 --> 00:07:42,520
None of your business.

197
00:07:45,730 --> 00:07:47,290
Don't you care

198
00:07:47,540 --> 00:07:48,980
how I know her?

199
00:07:50,110 --> 00:07:51,140
None of my business.

200
00:07:52,620 --> 00:07:53,330
Fine.

201
00:07:53,330 --> 00:07:54,580
[Zone 17]
[Testing Center]

202
00:07:53,390 --> 00:07:53,900
This way, please.

203
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:55,180
The report will be out

204
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:56,540
within five working days.

205
00:07:57,700 --> 00:07:58,220
Thank you.

206
00:07:58,460 --> 00:07:58,980
It's my pleasure.

207
00:07:58,980 --> 00:07:59,740
Goodbye, Director Meng.

208
00:08:07,130 --> 00:08:09,860
[I'll wait for you downstairs.]

209
00:08:13,170 --> 00:08:14,670
[Testing Center]

210
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:26,260
[Clinic] [Pharmacy] [Restaurant]

211
00:08:31,540 --> 00:08:32,010
Brother.

212
00:08:34,179 --> 00:08:35,140
You're done with your checkup?

213
00:08:35,620 --> 00:08:36,539
What do you want for lunch?

214
00:08:37,179 --> 00:08:38,340
Why didn't you change your clothes?

215
00:08:39,100 --> 00:08:40,789
I wanted to eat in the canteen.

216
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:42,820
I wanted to bring you out

217
00:08:42,820 --> 00:08:43,900
to eat something good.

218
00:08:44,430 --> 00:08:45,340
Brother,

219
00:08:45,420 --> 00:08:46,750
I'm busy, okay?

220
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:51,640
Are you looking down on our canteen?

221
00:08:52,100 --> 00:08:53,010
It's not that.

222
00:08:53,220 --> 00:08:54,460
I can have a taste.

223
00:08:55,260 --> 00:08:56,160
Do you remember when you were little,

224
00:08:56,450 --> 00:08:57,770
you often didn't have enough to eat,

225
00:08:58,030 --> 00:08:58,830
so I brought you out to eat

226
00:08:58,860 --> 00:08:59,630
secretly?

227
00:09:00,650 --> 00:09:01,450
I don't remember.

228
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:03,480
Really?

229
00:09:08,970 --> 00:09:10,110
You have to support us.

230
00:09:11,930 --> 00:09:12,970
We meet again?

231
00:09:15,660 --> 00:09:16,930
Why are you here?

232
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:21,780
Check up.

233
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,330
You are...?

234
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,450
I'm here for work.

235
00:09:25,170 --> 00:09:26,410
Let me introduce.

236
00:09:27,020 --> 00:09:27,750
Song Yan.

237
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:29,260
The Chief of our fire station.

238
00:09:29,570 --> 00:09:30,530
Meng Yanchen.

239
00:09:30,990 --> 00:09:31,980
Xu Qin's brother.

240
00:09:37,770 --> 00:09:38,670
Do you know each other?

241
00:09:39,020 --> 00:09:39,860
No.
No.

242
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:42,900
You can get to know each other then.

243
00:09:48,340 --> 00:09:48,940
Hello.

244
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:52,550
Hello.

245
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:58,080
Let's go.

246
00:09:58,710 --> 00:09:59,610
We'll be off.

247
00:10:25,520 --> 00:10:26,660
Deputy President Liu.

248
00:10:27,780 --> 00:10:28,610
President Fu.

249
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,180
Is Song Yan now

250
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:31,340
the Chief of a fire station?

251
00:10:35,930 --> 00:10:37,140
I don't know him.

252
00:10:41,550 --> 00:10:42,060
Right.

253
00:10:42,820 --> 00:10:43,740
You don't.

254
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:44,940
I misspoke.

255
00:10:45,370 --> 00:10:46,300
It's okay.

256
00:11:15,930 --> 00:11:19,320
[Yanbei Fire and Rescue Team]

257
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:24,300
Take your time.

258
00:11:24,300 --> 00:11:25,380
Read it carefully.

259
00:11:26,780 --> 00:11:28,620
This concerns the reputation of the hospital.

260
00:11:30,340 --> 00:11:31,460
It's also an opportunity

261
00:11:31,460 --> 00:11:32,620
for the Emergency Department to showcase yourselves.

262
00:11:38,010 --> 00:11:39,900
I know you don't care,

263
00:11:40,650 --> 00:11:42,060
but you should create opportunities

264
00:11:42,060 --> 00:11:43,460
for the young people under you.

265
00:11:49,020 --> 00:11:50,620
If you have any problems, feel free to voice them.

266
00:11:53,290 --> 00:11:54,850
I think

267
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:56,620
it's inappropriate for our doctors

268
00:11:56,620 --> 00:11:57,540
to live and train with firefighters.

269
00:11:58,340 --> 00:11:59,620
Besides, they want our doctors

270
00:11:59,620 --> 00:12:00,700
on the scene.

271
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:01,420
The scene of a fire

272
00:12:01,420 --> 00:12:02,740
is so complicated.

273
00:12:03,300 --> 00:12:04,900
Who can guarantee the doctors' safety?

274
00:12:10,460 --> 00:12:12,860
You've hit the nail on the head.

275
00:12:13,770 --> 00:12:14,820
How can we guarantee our doctors' safety

276
00:12:14,820 --> 00:12:15,820
at the scene?

277
00:12:16,220 --> 00:12:17,180
Shouldn't they have

278
00:12:17,180 --> 00:12:18,100
relevant knowledge?

279
00:12:18,330 --> 00:12:19,580
How can they gain relevant knowledge?

280
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:20,420
Shouldn't it begin

281
00:12:20,420 --> 00:12:21,700
from regular training?

282
00:12:22,180 --> 00:12:23,010
If you don't train them well,

283
00:12:23,010 --> 00:12:24,140
how can they treat casualties?

284
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,140
This is not

285
00:12:28,140 --> 00:12:29,340
what you should be thinking about.

286
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:30,340
Just think about

287
00:12:30,340 --> 00:12:31,500
who to choose.

288
00:12:32,380 --> 00:12:33,140
There's no need to think.

289
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:36,460
Send me there.

290
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:40,180
[Medicine Values Sincerity]

291
00:12:38,590 --> 00:12:39,780
I'm not joking with you.

292
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:42,130
If you have a problem

293
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:43,100
with President Wang's assignment

294
00:12:43,100 --> 00:12:44,150
you can talk to him directly.

295
00:12:44,170 --> 00:12:46,500
[Medicine Values Sincerity]

