00:36:31,780 --> 00:36:33,460
Do everyone know how to

888
00:36:33,540 --> 00:36:34,500
stop bleeding, bandage a wound,

889
00:36:34,500 --> 00:36:35,460
and perform CPR and 
mouth-to-mouth resuscitation?

890
00:36:38,820 --> 00:36:40,180
The new members don't know.

891
00:36:40,570 --> 00:36:42,540
Old members teammates should have a refresher.

892
00:36:43,380 --> 00:36:44,380
Let's learn them one by one.

893
00:36:44,900 --> 00:36:45,380
Alright.

894
00:36:45,860 --> 00:36:47,290
Today, let's learn

895
00:36:47,290 --> 00:36:48,020
how to stop bleeding and bandage a wound.

896
00:36:49,170 --> 00:36:49,980
But

897
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:52,950
I need a human dummy.

898
00:36:53,810 --> 00:36:54,980
Jiang Yi, you're up.

899
00:36:54,980 --> 00:36:55,620
Yes.

900
00:36:56,230 --> 00:36:56,820
Wait.

901
00:36:56,820 --> 00:36:57,570
Why are you going?

902
00:36:57,660 --> 00:36:58,210
Chief,

903
00:36:58,260 --> 00:37:00,300
Jiang is not good at bandaging wounds.

904
00:37:00,300 --> 00:37:02,140
You should be the dummy.

905
00:37:02,210 --> 00:37:02,940
Chief.

906
00:37:02,940 --> 00:37:04,340
My bandaging is really bad.

907
00:37:04,340 --> 00:37:05,500
I need to observe and learn more.

908
00:37:07,780 --> 00:37:09,420
Chief, I'm also bad at it.

909
00:37:09,860 --> 00:37:11,020
Let's clap!

910
00:37:13,420 --> 00:37:14,380
Bravo!

911
00:37:14,380 --> 00:37:15,220
Chief!

912
00:37:25,940 --> 00:37:26,620
Arterial bleeding

913
00:37:26,620 --> 00:37:27,940
is the most dangerous

914
00:37:27,940 --> 00:37:29,420
form of bleeding.

915
00:37:29,420 --> 00:37:31,260
The bleeding is fast and the volume is big.

916
00:37:31,300 --> 00:37:32,490
If we don't stop the bleeding in time,

917
00:37:32,490 --> 00:37:33,740
the victim's life might be in danger.

918
00:37:33,860 --> 00:37:35,850
That's why learning how to quickly stop arterial bleeding

919
00:37:35,940 --> 00:37:36,780
can buy time

920
00:37:36,780 --> 00:37:37,900
for the injured.

921
00:37:38,820 --> 00:37:39,420
Xu Xi.

922
00:37:47,500 --> 00:37:49,090
During a rescue,

923
00:37:49,220 --> 00:37:50,900
you can use a bandage or tourniquet

924
00:37:50,900 --> 00:37:52,620
to stop bleeding at the proximal endvof the artery.

925
00:37:54,060 --> 00:37:56,260
For lower limbs, tie it at the middle of the thigh.

926
00:37:57,740 --> 00:37:58,530
For upper limbs,

927
00:37:58,900 --> 00:38:00,160
tie it below the deltoid muscle.

928
00:38:03,760 --> 00:38:04,730
Take a look.

929
00:38:06,170 --> 00:38:07,160
It's right here.

930
00:38:10,370 --> 00:38:12,250
Distracted, Chief Song?

931
00:38:17,140 --> 00:38:18,090
Take note.

932
00:38:18,260 --> 00:38:19,380
Bandages and tourniquets

933
00:38:19,380 --> 00:38:21,020
must be loosened every 15 minutes

934
00:38:21,300 --> 00:38:22,740
so the tissue wouldn't be damaged due to ischemia.

935
00:38:27,540 --> 00:38:28,380
Chief Song.

936
00:38:31,220 --> 00:38:32,220
Take off your shirt.

937
00:38:33,980 --> 00:38:34,750
What?

938
00:38:35,630 --> 00:38:36,870
Take off your shirt.

939
00:38:55,550 --> 00:38:56,740
I'll bet you five kilometers.

940
00:38:56,760 --> 00:38:58,200
Chief and Dr. Xu still have a chance.

941
00:38:58,620 --> 00:38:59,660
I'll bet you ten kilometers.

942
00:38:59,700 --> 00:39:00,830
Before they have a chance,

943
00:39:00,900 --> 00:39:01,900
you'll get it coming to you.

944
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:09,780
When there is traumatic injury

945
00:39:09,780 --> 00:39:11,420
from car accidents, earthquakes, or fires,

946
00:39:11,620 --> 00:39:13,020
the injured often

947
00:39:13,020 --> 00:39:14,100
suffer from pneumothorax.

948
00:39:14,140 --> 00:39:15,180
If we don't perform

949
00:39:15,180 --> 00:39:16,220
aspiration,

950
00:39:16,260 --> 00:39:17,500
the victim might die quickly.

951
00:39:18,340 --> 00:39:19,340
Next, I'm going to talk about

952
00:39:19,340 --> 00:39:20,740
the symptoms of pneumothorax.

953
00:39:22,140 --> 00:39:22,680
First,

954
00:39:22,820 --> 00:39:24,220
the victim will have extreme breathing difficulty.

955
00:39:24,380 --> 00:39:26,380
Those who have severe hypoxemia might even suffocate.

956
00:39:27,050 --> 00:39:27,620
Second,

957
00:39:28,250 --> 00:39:29,830
the chest will swell near the wound

958
00:39:30,100 --> 00:39:31,700
and appear higher than the other side.

959
00:39:32,020 --> 00:39:33,260
As long as these two symptoms occur,

960
00:39:33,260 --> 00:39:35,060
we need to perform aspiration immediately.

961
00:39:35,380 --> 00:39:36,420
In an emergency,

962
00:39:36,500 --> 00:39:38,740
you can use a thick needle

963
00:39:38,900 --> 00:39:39,780
to make a puncture

964
00:39:39,780 --> 00:39:41,530
at the intersection between

965
00:39:42,260 --> 00:39:43,300
the second intercostal space and the collar bone.

966
00:39:43,420 --> 00:39:44,490
You can come and try.

967
00:39:45,020 --> 00:39:46,060
Well, I...

968
00:39:46,300 --> 00:39:47,010
Not you.

969
00:39:48,340 --> 00:39:49,660
Supervisor, you first.

970
00:39:49,700 --> 00:39:50,380
Okay.

971
00:39:58,740 --> 00:39:59,580
Hurry up.

972
00:40:00,460 --> 00:40:01,540
This is the first intercostal space.

973
00:40:01,900 --> 00:40:02,940
This is the second intercostal space.

974
00:40:03,410 --> 00:40:04,540
The intersection is here.

975
00:40:07,220 --> 00:40:08,300
Good. Next.

976
00:40:09,020 --> 00:40:09,820
Let me do it.

977
00:40:09,990 --> 00:40:11,710
Sorry, Chief.

978
00:40:13,860 --> 00:40:14,700
Collarbone.

979
00:40:15,860 --> 00:40:17,140
Here. Here, right?

980
00:40:17,220 --> 00:40:18,020
This is the first rib.

981
00:40:18,330 --> 00:40:19,250
This is the second rib.

982
00:40:21,300 --> 00:40:22,060
I've got it.

983
00:40:25,140 --> 00:40:25,690
Alright.

984
00:40:25,860 --> 00:40:26,900
That's all for the demonstration.

985
00:40:27,140 --> 00:40:28,340
I haven’t…

986
00:40:28,660 --> 00:40:29,660
Why did he leave?

987
00:40:29,680 --> 00:40:30,240
The teaching aid is gone.

988
00:40:30,340 --> 00:40:32,660
Chief Song has such a nice body.

989
00:40:32,740 --> 00:40:33,890
You're too boy-crazy.

990
00:40:33,890 --> 00:40:35,380
Calm down.

991
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:37,250
Why did he run away?

992
00:40:37,620 --> 00:40:38,460
Come, Pipi.

993
00:40:38,460 --> 00:40:39,620
You're the dummy now. Take off your shirt.

994
00:40:39,900 --> 00:40:40,700
I shouldn't...

995
00:40:40,720 --> 00:40:41,380
Come on.

996
00:40:41,380 --> 00:40:42,620
Let's clap for him!
